The paper deals with the complexity of conjunctive query evaluation, which is a fundamental problem in database theory and falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper heavily relies on graph theory and introduces a new notion called graph deconstruction, which is related to tree decomposition. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of pebble games, which is a common technique in logic and model checking, and hence it may be classified under the categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
